@DATABASE "ilbmtoppm.guide"
@INDEX "ImageEditor.guide/INDEX"
@FONT helvetica.font 13
@SMARTWRAP

@NODE MAIN "ImageEditor - Loader: IFF [ilbmtoppm]"
@TOC "Loader.guide/MAIN"

@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}IFF@{UB}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{B}Convert an IFF-Picture file into a portable pixmap.@{UB}@{LINE}
@{PAR}Reads an IFF-ILBM, IFF-RGBN, IFF-RGB8 or IFF-PBM file as input. Produces a portable pixmap as output.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
@{B}Color of Transparence to@{UB}@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 12}
    Write transparent pixels in this color instead of their colormap entry.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
@{B}Extract Colormap only@{UB}@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 12}
    Extract only the colormap from the input file. The resulting PPM file will be in P3 ASCII format, and will be written to »Colormaps/«.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
@{B}Extract Maskfile too@{UB}@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 12}
    Generate a mask file from a mask plane (ILBM) or transparent color entry (ILBM and IFF-PBM),
or genlock bits (RGBN/RGB8) and write it. This is a normal PBM image, the same size as the PPM output file.
A pixel value of WHITE in the mask file means the corresponding in the output file is considered to be transparent,
BLACK indicates an opaque pixel (think of the output file casting a shadow on a white screen).@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}See also the @{" IFF " LINK "ppmtoilbm.guide/MAIN"} saver.@{LINE}
@{PAR}[@{B}ilbmtoppm@{UB}] @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{I}Copyright (C) 1995 by Ingo Wilken @{UI}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE
